    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Aztec vestments comprising articulated pieces of iridescent shell sewn in a pattern on a textile support. Derived from Nahuatl for "joined mother -of-pearl." Many examples are made from the Pacific mollusk Pinctada mazatlanica.</Note_Text>
